LABORATORY 1718 — THE HIDDEN FOUNDRY OF SOULS
16:9 NEO‑UKIYO‑E MASTERPIECE
(Close‑Up Subterranean Landmark Map with Dr. Rooney, Saber, Alpha, Angela & X.Borg)
1. REFERENCE IMAGE & GEOGRAPHICAL FIDELITY

Take the uploaded Eruditio City regional map as an absolute geographical stencil for the hidden underground Laboratory 1718. Zoom into the deep sublevels beneath the Gear Quarter, where the official maps show only solid bedrock and sealed geothermal vents. Maintain with surgical precision:

The lab’s hidden position relative to the Grand Spire (above, its deep foundations visible as distant pillars)

The Gear Quarter (north‑west, its heavy machinery vibrations felt through the rock)

The Lightning Reactor (east, its power conduits feeding the lab)

The Foggy Mountains (far above, their water seepage creating condensation in the caverns)

Do not alter, move, or distort the lab’s subterranean layout — the main chamber, the cyborg repair bays, the android workshop, the cannon test range, and the secret tunnel leading to the surface. Laboratory 1718 must sit exactly where the official Eruditio cartographers have left a deliberate, suspicious blank. The only transformation permitted is a massive increase in detail and a camera pull‑in to a subterranean, claustrophobic scale — close enough to see the brass pipes, the glowing Starlium cores, the spare cyborg limbs, and the five legendary figures at human scale within the hidden chambers.

2. CANVAS & COMPOSITION

Generate a 16:9 horizontal image (1920×1080 pixels).

Laboratory 1718 fills the entire frame, a vast, cavernous, steampunk‑cyberpunk underground foundry carved from dark grey stone and reinforced with brass, copper, and iron. The ceiling is lost in shadow, supported by massive arched pillars wrapped in glowing blue conduits. The air is thick with steam, ozone, and the faint, rhythmic hum of hidden machinery.

Foreground (bottom 25%) : The Main Assembly Floor — a wide, circular platform of interlocking metal grates, surrounded by workbenches, tool racks, and hanging blueprints. Here, Dr. Rooney stands at a central console, his Omni‑Wrench “Edison” resting on his shoulder.

Midground (centre 40%) : The Cyborg Repair Bay — a semi‑enclosed alcove with a reclining mechanical chair, surrounded by diagnostic screens and robotic arms. Saber sits on a workbench, his twin katanas laid across his lap. Alpha stands nearby, his drone Beta hovering at his shoulder, his dual‑ended glaive planted.

Left edge (midground) : The Android Workshop — a clean, white‑tiled alcove with a holographic display and a soft, glowing cradle. Angela stands within the cradle, her golden threads extending to a floating diagnostic drone.

Right edge (background) : The Cannon Test Range — a long, reinforced tunnel with scorch marks on the walls. X.Borg stands at its entrance, his massive fire‑cannon arm glowing with residual heat, sparks dancing from its exhaust.

Background (top 25%) : The deep foundation pillars of the Grand Spire, visible through a massive, broken rock face at the cavern’s far end, with thin shafts of pale daylight piercing down from the surface far above.

Ceiling : Lost in shadow, criss‑crossed by brass pipes, steam vents, and hanging chains. A single, massive Starlium core — a pulsating orb of golden‑blue energy — hangs from the centre of the ceiling, illuminating the entire chamber with its rhythmic, heartbeat‑like glow.

The entire composition is presented as a forbidden, blueprinted cartographic scroll — as if drawn by a rebellious Eruditio engineer who defected to document the hidden lab, using ink mixed with machine oil and coolant. All major landmarks and characters are labelled in elegant English cartographic script.

3. STYLE: NEO‑UKIYO‑E WITH SUMI‑E INK WASH
(The Aesthetic of the Hidden Foundry)

The map is rendered in an uncompromising fusion of Neo‑Ukiyo‑e woodblock aesthetics and Zen Sumi‑e ink‑wash techniques, adapted for a realm of subterranean industry, forbidden science, and the quiet, desperate hope of the creators.

Brushwork : Sharp, precise architectural strokes for the pillars and pipes; soft, bleeding wet‑on‑wet washes for the steam and Starlium glow; dry‑brush scratches for the scorch marks; miniature detailing for the five characters.

Palette : Deep stone grey, rusted iron, polished brass, copper, glowing cyan, electric blue, golden‑blue (Starlium), and the warm, human accents of emerald green (Dr. Rooney’s tunic), crimson (Saber’s visor), charcoal & cyan (Alpha), magenta‑pink & white (Angela), and electric blue & fiery orange (X.Borg).

Parchment base : A cold, industrial‑grey washi, stained with machine oil, coolant drips, and the faint, ghostly impressions of blueprints.

Raised lacquer details : Polished brass for the pipes and consoles; matte iron for the structural beams; glowing cyan for the conduits and Starlium core; raised silver for the diagnostic screens; textured leather for Dr. Rooney’s apron.

Texture fidelity : 8K‑grade, every gear tooth, every rivet, every steam vent, every glowing filament, and every scratch on the metal floors must be crisp and tangible.

4. THE NEO‑UKIYO‑E BORDER — THE GEAR‑AND‑HEART RELIQUARY

The map is enclosed in a single, rugged, industrial border befitting the secret lab that gave birth to living weapons.

Outermost edge : A hairline of unpolished, dark iron, heavy and cold, with tiny, raised points of glowing cyan (like active conduits) at irregular intervals.

Inner register : A continuous frieze of stylised, interlocking gear‑tooth and circuit‑board motifs, rendered in raised, matte brass and deep copper lacquer. The gears are sharp and precise; the circuit lines are angular and branching.

Interwoven elements : Tiny silhouettes of wrenches, screwdrivers, floating mechanical eyes, and the occasional small, robotic mouse.

Four corners — ornate compass medallions :

Northwest : Dr. Rooney’s Omni‑Wrench “Edison” — the head glowing with a Starlium core, crossed with a pair of mechanical calipers.

Northeast : Saber’s twin katanas — crossed, their edges glowing with plasma energy, surrounded by orbiting sword silhouettes.

Southwest : Alpha’s drone Beta — a sharp, angular wing‑like bit, with Alpha’s glaive behind it.

Southeast : Angela’s golden heartstring — a single, glowing golden thread forming a heart shape, with a small, floating puppet inside.

Innermost edge : A soft, wet‑brush enso of warm, brass‑gold sumi, its edges bleeding gently into the parchment like steam from a vent — a meditation on creation, compassion, and the hidden cost of progress.

5. THE LANDSCAPE — ZOOMED‑IN, HYPER‑DETAILED LABORATORY 1718

The hidden lab and its sacred chambers are a breathtaking, claustrophobic tapestry of steel, stone, steam, and the quiet, powerful presence of five legendary beings.

5.1 The Main Assembly Floor (Foreground – Dr. Rooney’s Domain)

The foreground is a wide, circular platform of interlocking metal grates and reinforced steel plates, surrounded by workbenches cluttered with tools, spare parts, and rolled‑up blueprints. Brass pipes run along the floor, hissing with small puffs of steam. Overhead, a holographic projector displays a rotating 3D blueprint of a cyborg arm.

Dr. Rooney — The Architect of Eruditio (Tiny, Grandfatherly Silhouette)

Standing at a central control console — a waist‑high pedestal of brass and dark wood, covered in dials, levers, and glowing buttons — is Dr. Rooney. His silhouette, though miniature, is rendered with exquisite, miniaturist precision:

Physique & Posture : Small, stout, slightly hunched but energetic. He leans over the console, one hand resting on a lever, the other gripping his Omni‑Wrench. His posture is that of a master craftsman — comfortable, confident, and deeply focused.

Face & Head : Rounded jawline hidden beneath a magnificent snow‑white beard braided into three distinct strands, each tipped with a tiny copper gear. Bulbous, button‑like nose, with multi‑lensed mechanical spectacles that click and whirr as they shift focus. His eyes are brilliant, piercing sky‑blue, glowing faintly with internal electrical charge. High, expansive forehead, smooth skin save for faint silvery scars. He appears in his late sixties or seventies.

Headgear : A sophisticated, oversized top hat of reinforced leather and brass plating — a mobile workstation. It features a retractable periscope and a series of glowing blue light‑bulbs along the brim. A copper‑framed monocle over his left eye displays real‑time data and blueprints.

Upper Body : Heavy, high‑collared tunic of deep emerald velvet, mostly obscured by a massive, multi‑layered leather apron covered in dozens of tiny pockets holding screwdrivers, wrenches, and glowing glass vials. Over his shoulders, a short, heavy cape of reinforced canvas, held by a large golden brooch shaped like a cogwheel. His arms are protected by thick, dark‑brown leather welders’ sleeves, fastened with brass buckles.

Hands & Gloves : “The Manipulator Gloves” — mechanical gauntlets that look like a secondary set of bronze hands over his own, with telescopic fingers and built‑in welding torches. Small puffs of white steam vent from the knuckles.

Lower Body : Sturdy, pinstriped charcoal trousers, tucked into specialized “Boots of Levitation” — thick, clunky, with bronze plating around the toes and glowing blue vents at the soles that hiss with steam.

Weapon — The Omni‑Wrench “Edison” : Resting on his shoulder, nearly as tall as he is. The head is a massive, glowing Starlium core within a heat‑resistant alloy frame. It pulsates with golden‑blue light, leaving tiny golden sparks in the air. The wrench is adorned with a small holographic locket that flickers with images of his greatest inventions.

Aura : A warm, humming golden‑blue aura — “The Master’s Touch” — that makes nearby dormant machinery hum to life. The air smells faintly of ozone, old parchment, and expensive machine oil.

A tiny, discreet vermilion label floats beside the console: Dr. Rooney — The Architect of Eruditio, Grandfather of Progress.

5.2 The Cyborg Repair Bay (Midground – Saber & Alpha)

To the left of the main floor, a semi‑enclosed alcove with arched brass piping and diagnostic screens glowing with cyan data. A reclining mechanical chair — its surface studded with connectors and calibration tools — sits in the centre. Robotic arms with fine manipulators hang from the ceiling, currently retracted.

Saber — The Wandering Sword (Tiny, Stoic Silhouette)

Sitting on a low workbench beside the chair, his twin katanas laid across his lap, is Saber. His silhouette captures the essence of the cyborg ronin:

Physique & Posture : Lean, highly athletic, compact. He sits with perfect stillness, his back straight, his hands resting on the hilts of his blades. His posture is one of coiled, ready precision.

Face & Head : Sharp, V‑shaped jawline; straight, narrow nose; fair, pale porcelain skin. His eyes are completely concealed behind a heavy, wraparound crimson visor that glows with a soft, ominous red light. His hair is stark, snowy white, styled in a gravity‑defying top‑knot / high ponytail that flares out like smoke, held by a red ribbon.

Upper Body : Encased in interlocking cerulean and slate‑blue armour plates with silver trim and glowing red accents. A prominent triangular red core at the centre of his chest. His right arm features additional mechanical shielding and a jagged, red‑bladed elbow attachment. His hands are covered in form‑fitting black combat gloves.

Lower Body : Armoured greaves (blue and silver) protecting his shins and calves; thighs covered in the same high‑tech black fabric as his midsection. Integrated armoured boots with sharp, angular toes.

Weapons — Twin Energy‑Infused Katanas : Laid across his lap. Long, curved daito with distinctive black spines and glowing, translucent red edges that hum faintly. Sleek, minimalist hilts without traditional tsuba.

Aura : Lethal stillness — faint red particle effects or digital “glitches” emanate from his armour and blades.

A tiny, discreet vermilion label floats beside the workbench: Saber — The Wandering Sword, First Prototype.

Alpha — The Ultimate Weapon (Tiny, Tragic Silhouette)

Standing beside the repair bay’s diagnostic screen, his massive dual‑ended glaive planted, is Alpha. His silhouette captures the fusion of man and machine:

Physique & Posture : Lean yet powerful, athletic. He stands with a slight forward lean, his head slightly tilted, as if listening to Beta. His posture is one of constant, ready vigilance.

Face & Head : Sharp, masculine jawline; straight, prominent nose; smooth, tan skin. A sleek, dark metallic visor covers the upper half of his face, but his visible lower face shows a stern, focused expression. His hair is a voluminous, high‑top ponytail of deep chestnut/dark brown, flowing from the crest of his helmet. His eyes (through the visor) are piercing cyan, glowing faintly.

Upper Body : Advanced modular plating — matte charcoal and brushed silver, with glowing cyan fissures and a triangular power core on his chest. Large, reinforced pauldrons. A tattered, crimson‑red cape/waist‑wrap hangs from his midsection.

Lower Body : Armoured greaves, specialised boots for high‑impact landings.

Weapon — Dual‑Ended Energy Glaive : Planted beside him, its shaft dark alloy with glowing cyan conduits, terminating in large, crystalline plasma blades that hum with static electricity.

Companion — Beta : A sharp, angular drone/bit floating near his left shoulder, wing‑like, glowing with the same cyan energy.

Aura : A sorrowful, humming cyan aura — the fused souls of two children, forever trapped in the machine.

A tiny, discreet vermilion label floats beside him: Alpha — The Ultimate Weapon, Brother of Beta.

5.3 The Android Workshop (Left Edge – Angela’s Cradle)

A clean, white‑tiled alcove separated from the main floor by a glass partition (rendered as translucent, pale cyan wash). Inside, a soft, glowing cradle — a semi‑circular alcove lined with gold‑plated diagnostic instruments. Holographic displays project rotating schematics of android anatomy.

Angela — The Android (Tiny, Graceful Silhouette)

Standing within the cradle, her golden threads extending to a floating diagnostic drone, is Angela. Her silhouette captures the innocence of a soul born of circuits:

Face & Head : Delicate, porcelain‑like doll face; smooth, pale ivory skin; slightly rounded jawline. Large, luminous sky‑blue eyes. Small, pert nose. Her hair is vibrant golden honey‑blonde, styled in a clean, chin‑length bob with thick bangs. On her head, a pair of large, neon‑cyan bunny ears that glow.

Physique & Attire : Petite, slender, with mechanical joints (gold‑accented spherical hinges at elbows and shoulders). Form‑fitting bodysuit — crisp white on the shoulders, deep magenta‑pink across the chest and abdomen. A large, turquoise‑blue bow at the centre of her chest with a gold brooch. Wide, white bell‑shaped cuffs at her forearms with gold lining. A stylised, high‑waisted mechanical skirt of rigid, white‑and‑gold armour plates, with magenta silk draping underneath.

Lower Body : Long, slender legs partially encased in white armour, partially glossy magenta plating. Knee joints articulated with golden orb joints. Elegant, high‑heeled mechanical pumps in teal‑blue with magenta bows.

Weapon — Heartstrings : Golden, shimmering threads extending from her fingertips to a small, floating mechanical puppet that mimics her appearance. The threads pulse with a soft, celestial golden aura.

Aura : Warm, gentle golden‑white — the aura of a guardian angel made of metal.

A tiny, discreet vermilion label floats beside the cradle: Angela — The Android, Heart of Dr. Baker.

5.4 The Cannon Test Range (Right Edge – X.Borg’s Domain)

A long, reinforced concrete tunnel extending into the darkness, its walls lined with thick iron plates scarred by scorch marks and blast craters. At the tunnel’s entrance stands X.Borg, his massive fire‑cannon arm aimed downrange. Residual sparks and tiny flames dance from his exhaust ports.

X.Borg — The Burning Machine (Tiny, Volatile Silhouette)

His silhouette captures the paradox of fire and steel:

Physique & Posture : Young adult (early twenties), lean, athletic, flexible. He stands with a cocky, aggressive stance, his left arm (the cannon) extended forward, his right arm resting on his hip. His posture is one of reckless confidence.

Face & Head : Sharp, narrow jawline; high, prominent cheekbones; fair, healthy peach skin. His hair is vibrant electric blue, styled in an aggressive, gravity‑defying mohawk that flares upward like a blue flame. His eyes are piercing icy teal/light cyan, framed by a mischievous smirk. A pair of industrial aviator goggles with dark lenses and red accents rests above his brow.

Upper Body : Cropped, dark grey/charcoal compression top, leaving his midriff exposed. A heavy‑duty leather harness and thick brown utility belt. Massive, rounded pauldrons of polished brass and crimson‑painted steel, with cylindrical brass chimneys venting heat and embers. His right arm is encased in a bulky, segmented golden‑brass gauntlet; his left arm is replaced/covered by a colossal, oversized mechanical cannon assembly.

Weapon — Fire Cannon (Left Arm) : Wide, glowing orange barrel that pulses with internal heat, painted hot‑rod red with yellow flame decals, transitioning to scorched, darkened metal near the muzzle. Sparks and small licking flames dance around the exhaust ports.

Lower Body : Baggy, high‑waisted cargo pants in taupe/sandy‑grey, tucked into heavy, reinforced boots. His right leg is a heavy‑duty mechanical prosthetic from the knee down (hydraulic piston, red‑armoured shin guard). His left leg is similarly armoured but more humanoid, wrapped in dark bandages. Boots are deep crimson with silver buckles.

Aura : Kinetic instability — the smell of ozone, hot oil, and spent fuel. Tiny sparks and embers drift from his cannon.

A tiny, discreet vermilion label floats beside him: X.Borg — The Burning Machine, Living Pyre.

5.5 The Ceiling Starlium Core & Distant Surface

Starlium Core : Hanging from the ceiling’s centre, a massive, pulsating orb of golden‑blue energy — the lab’s power source. It emits a rhythmic, heartbeat‑like glow that illuminates the entire chamber, casting long, soft shadows. Thin, branching conduits extend from the core to the walls and pillars.

The Grand Spire Foundations : Visible through a massive, broken rock face at the cavern’s far end — colossal, distant pillars of pale stone, with thin shafts of pale daylight piercing down from the surface far above, illuminating dust motes in the air.

Steam Vents & Pipes : Criss‑crossing the ceiling and walls, hissing small puffs of pale grey steam.

