7. JAPANESE CALLIGRAPHY — POETIC TITLE & INVOCATION

At the top‑centre of the map, floating within the mana aurora, is a bold, vertical column of Japanese calligraphy in gyōsho script, using an ink of violet‑flecked cyan that shimmers like the floating crystals.

Column 1 (Main Title):

text
秘法科学アカデミー — 魔導と機械の交差点
